Note:
PHP Semantic Analyzer - scope and name analysis over the Stage-A dict-AST.

This pass walks the dictionary/list AST produced by php_parser.runa and performs
real two-phase semantic analysis:

Phase 1 (collection) records every top-level declaration name: namespaces,
classes / interfaces / traits / enums, and functions, plus the constant set, so
forward references resolve regardless of definition order.

Phase 2 (resolution) walks every member resolving name references and per-scope
variable bindings: function/method/closure/arrow_fn parameters introduce bindings
that are restored on scope exit; $this / self / static / parent are recognised
inside class members; foreach key/value vars, catch vars, global/static vars, and
list() destructuring targets all bind; assignment targets bind their variable.
Unbound bare variables are recorded as warnings (PHP creates variables on first
assignment, so an unbound read is suspicious but not provably wrong); unresolved
class-name references that are not built-ins are recorded as warnings; genuine
structural problems (a class with an empty name, a function with no name) are
recorded as errors.

The AST is read entirely through the Stage-A contract documented at the top of
php_parser.runa: get_ast_attribute(node, key) for named attributes,
get_ast_children(node) for positional children, and the "node_type" string
attribute on every node.

Dependencies:
- compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/php/php_parser.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/php/php_parser.runa" as Parser
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as ListOps
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ANALYZER STATE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The analyzer threads four lists through the recursive walk: defined_names (the
names of classes/interfaces/traits/enums/functions/constants declared across the
program), bound_variables (the variable names currently in scope), errors, and
warnings. Flat name lists keep binding scope cheap to save/restore around function
and closure boundaries: a callable records the bound-list length on entry and
truncates back to it on exit so parameters never leak between sibling callables.
@End Reasoning
Type called "PhpSemanticAnalyzer":
    defined_names as Integer       Note: List of declaration-name strings
    bound_variables as Integer     Note: List of in-scope variable-name strings
    errors as Integer              Note: List of error message strings
    warnings as Integer            Note: List of warning message strings
End Type

@Reasoning:
Allocates a 32-byte analyzer with four freshly-created lists so each analysis run
starts with empty scope and diagnostic state. Returns 0 on allocation failure so
callers can guard.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_php_semantic_analyzer" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a fresh PHP semantic analyzer

    Let analyzer be proc allocate from Layout with 32
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let defined_names be proc create from ListOps
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0, defined_names

    Let bound_variables be proc create from ListOps
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8, bound_variables

    Let errors be proc create from ListOps
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16, errors

    Let warnings be proc create from ListOps
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24, warnings

    Return analyzer
End Process

@Reasoning:
Releases the analyzer struct. The four lists are borrowed by callers that may read
diagnostics afterward, so only the 32-byte struct is freed here; callers own the
analysis lifetime.
@End Reasoning
Process called "destroy_php_semantic_analyzer" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with analyzer
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SMALL ACCESSORS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Reads a node's string node_type attribute through the Stage-A accessor.
@End Reasoning
Process called "node_type_of" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_ast_attribute from Parser with node, "node_type"
End Process

@Reasoning:
Reads a named AST attribute; null-guards the node.
@End Reasoning
Process called "attr" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc get_ast_attribute from Parser with node, key
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when a node's node_type string equals tag.
@End Reasoning
Process called "node_is" takes node as Integer, tag as Integer returns Integer:
    Let nt be proc node_type_of with node
    If nt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, tag
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records a semantic error message on the analyzer's error list.
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_semantic_error" takes analyzer as Integer, message as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let errors be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16
    proc list_append from ListOps with errors, message
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records a semantic warning message on the analyzer's warning list.
@End Reasoning
Process called "add_semantic_warning" takes analyzer as Integer, message as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let warnings be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
    proc list_append from ListOps with warnings, message
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the accumulated error list for the driver.
@End Reasoning
Process called "get_semantic_errors" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 16
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the accumulated warning list for the driver.
@End Reasoning
Process called "get_semantic_warnings" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 24
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SCOPE MANAGEMENT
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Records a declared name (class/interface/trait/enum/function/constant) so later
reference resolution can recognise it. Duplicate names are permitted; the table is
a definition set, not a uniqueness check.
@End Reasoning
Process called "define_name" takes analyzer as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let defs be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    proc list_append from ListOps with defs, name
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Binds a variable name into the current scope (a parameter, a foreach var, a catch
var, a global/static var, an assignment target, or a list() target). Records the
name on the bound list.
@End Reasoning
Process called "bind_variable" takes analyzer as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let bound be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    proc list_append from ListOps with bound, name
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the current depth of the binding scope (the bound-variable list length). A
callable saves this on entry and truncates back to it on exit so parameters do not
leak across sibling callables.
@End Reasoning
Process called "scope_mark" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let bound be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Return proc list_length from ListOps with bound
End Process

@Reasoning:
Truncates the binding scope back to a previously-recorded mark by rebuilding the
bound-variable list with only the entries below the mark. Because list.runa has no
in-place truncate primitive, we build a fresh list of the surviving prefix and
install it as the analyzer's bound list. This restores the enclosing scope when a
callable exits.
@End Reasoning
Process called "scope_restore" takes analyzer as Integer, mark as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let bound be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Let count be proc list_length from ListOps with bound

    If count is less than or equal to mark:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let rebuilt be proc create from ListOps
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than mark:
        Let name be proc list_get from ListOps with bound, i
        proc list_append from ListOps with rebuilt, name
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8, rebuilt
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when a variable name is currently in scope. Linear scan over the bound
list comparing with string_equals. PHP's superglobals ($GLOBALS, $_GET, $_POST,
$_SERVER, $_SESSION, $_COOKIE, $_REQUEST, $_FILES, $_ENV) and the implicit $this
are always considered bound.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_variable_bound" takes analyzer as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If proc is_superglobal with name:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let bound be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 8
    Let count be proc list_length from ListOps with bound
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let bn be proc list_get from ListOps with bound, i
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with bn, name
        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when a variable name is one of PHP's automatically-available variables:
the superglobals and $this. These are bound implicitly in every scope.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_superglobal" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "$this":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "$GLOBALS":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "$_GET":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "$_POST":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "$_SERVER":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "$_SESSION":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "$_COOKIE":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "$_REQUEST":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "$_FILES":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "$_ENV":
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when a class-name reference resolves to a recognised PHP built-in or
reserved class/keyword: self / static / parent and the common SPL / engine
exception and core classes. References to these are not flagged as unresolved.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_builtin_class" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "self":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "static":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "parent":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "Exception":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "Throwable":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "Error":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "RuntimeException":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "InvalidArgumentException":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "LogicException":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "TypeError":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "ValueError":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "stdClass":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "Closure":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "ArrayObject":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "Iterator":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "IteratorAggregate":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "Countable":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with name, "Generator":
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
True (1) when a name is one of those declared across the program. Linear scan over
the definition set.
@End Reasoning
Process called "is_name_defined" takes analyzer as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let defs be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 0
    Let count be proc list_length from ListOps with defs
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let dn be proc list_get from ListOps with defs, i
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with dn, name
        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TOP-LEVEL ANALYSIS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Entry point. Performs a two-phase analysis over the "program" root's body. Phase 1
collects every top-level declaration name (recursing into namespace bodies) so
forward references resolve. Phase 2 walks every member resolving references against
the collected definitions and per-callable binding scopes. A null AST is a no-op
success.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_php_ast" takes analyzer as Integer, ast as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze the PHP AST for scope/name correctness

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If ast is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let body be proc attr with ast, "body"
    If body is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Phase 1 - collect declaration names for forward references
    proc collect_definitions_in_list with analyzer, body

    Note: Phase 2 - resolve references node by node
    proc analyze_node_list with analyzer, body
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Phase-1 collector: records class/interface/trait/enum/function names so the resolve
phase recognises references regardless of order. Recurses into namespace bodies
(declarations inside a namespace block are still visible by their unqualified name
within the analysis). Other nodes contribute no top-level definitions.
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_definitions" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let nt be proc node_type_of with node
    If nt is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "namespace":
        Let nbody be proc attr with node, "body"
        proc collect_definitions_in_list with analyzer, nbody
        Return 1
    End If

    Let is_class be proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "class"
    If is_class is equal to 1:
        proc collect_named with analyzer, node
        Return 1
    End If
    Let is_iface be proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "interface"
    If is_iface is equal to 1:
        proc collect_named with analyzer, node
        Return 1
    End If
    Let is_trait be proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "trait"
    If is_trait is equal to 1:
        proc collect_named with analyzer, node
        Return 1
    End If
    Let is_enum be proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "enum"
    If is_enum is equal to 1:
        proc collect_named with analyzer, node
        Return 1
    End If
    Let is_fn be proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "function"
    If is_fn is equal to 1:
        proc collect_named with analyzer, node
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records a node's "name" attribute into the definition set when present.
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_named" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let name be proc attr with node, "name"
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc define_name with analyzer, name
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Collects definitions from every node in a list. Null-safe.
@End Reasoning
Process called "collect_definitions_in_list" takes analyzer as Integer, lst as Integer returns Integer:
    If lst is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from ListOps with lst
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let member be proc list_get from ListOps with lst, i
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc collect_definitions with analyzer, member
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: NODE RESOLUTION WALK
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Central resolution dispatcher. Declarations open the structures whose members need
their own scope handling; callables open binding scopes; control-flow nodes that
introduce bindings (foreach, catch, global, static) handle them specially; leaf
variables and names go through reference resolution; every other node recurses into
its sub-expressions generically. Returns 1 for every node; diagnostics accumulate
on the analyzer rather than aborting the walk.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_node" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let nt be proc node_type_of with node
    If nt is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "namespace":
        Let nbody be proc attr with node, "body"
        Return proc analyze_node_list with analyzer, nbody
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "class":
        Return proc analyze_type_decl with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "interface":
        Return proc analyze_type_decl with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "trait":
        Return proc analyze_type_decl with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "enum":
        Return proc analyze_type_decl with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "function":
        Return proc analyze_callable with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "method":
        Return proc analyze_callable with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "closure":
        Return proc analyze_closure with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "arrow_fn":
        Return proc analyze_callable with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "foreach":
        Return proc analyze_foreach with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "catch_clause":
        Return proc analyze_catch with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "global":
        Return proc analyze_var_binding_list with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "static_var":
        Return proc analyze_static_var with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "assign":
        Return proc analyze_assign with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "variable":
        Return proc resolve_variable with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "name":
        Return proc resolve_name with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "member":
        Return proc analyze_member with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "static_member":
        Return proc analyze_static_member with analyzer, node
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "pair":
        Note: a pair's key is a STRING; only its value is a sub-expression.
        Let pval be proc attr with node, "value"
        If pval is not equal to 0:
            proc analyze_node with analyzer, pval
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Leaf literal nodes carry their payload as a STRING ("value"), not as a
    Note: sub-node. They must terminate here so the generic walk never reads a raw
    Note: string attribute as if it were an AST node pointer (which dereferences
    Note: garbage). int/float/string/bool/null carry no sub-expressions.
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "int":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "float":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "string":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "bool":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "null":
        Return 1
    End If
    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "inline_html":
        Return 1
    End If

    Return proc analyze_generic with analyzer, node
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes every node in a list. Null-safe.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_node_list" takes analyzer as Integer, lst as Integer returns Integer:
    If lst is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from ListOps with lst
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let item be proc list_get from ListOps with lst, i
        If item is not equal to 0:
            proc analyze_node with analyzer, item
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A class/interface/trait/enum with an empty name is a structural error. Otherwise
its members are analyzed: methods open their own scopes, while properties and
constants resolve their default/value expressions at the class scope.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_type_decl" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let name be proc attr with node, "name"
    If name is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "type declaration has no name"
        Return 1
    End If
    Let name_len be proc string_length from StringCore with name
    If name_len is equal to 0:
        proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "type declaration has an empty name"
        Return 1
    End If

    Let members be proc attr with node, "members"
    proc analyze_node_list with analyzer, members
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A function/method/arrow_fn opens a fresh binding scope. A function/method with no
name is a structural error. Parameters bind their variable names (and a promoted
property param binds $this->name implicitly via the param itself); param defaults
are resolved at the enclosing scope before binding. The body is then resolved with
the parameters in scope. On exit the scope is restored so the next callable starts
clean.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_callable" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let nt be proc node_type_of with node
    Let is_arrow be proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "arrow_fn"
    Let is_closure be proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "closure"

    If is_arrow is equal to 0:
        If is_closure is equal to 0:
            Let name be proc attr with node, "name"
            If name is equal to 0:
                proc add_semantic_error with analyzer, "callable has no name"
                Return 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let mark be proc scope_mark with analyzer

    Let params be proc attr with node, "params"
    proc bind_params with analyzer, params

    Let body be proc attr with node, "body"
    If body is not equal to 0:
        Let body_nt be proc node_type_of with body
        Let body_is_block be proc string_equals from StringCore with body_nt, "block"
        If body_is_block is equal to 1:
            Let inner be proc attr with body, "body"
            proc analyze_node_list with analyzer, inner
        Otherwise:
            Note: arrow_fn body is a single expression.
            proc analyze_node with analyzer, body
        End If
    End If

    proc scope_restore with analyzer, mark
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A closure opens a fresh binding scope. Its parameters bind, and its use(...)
captures bind (a captured variable is in scope inside the closure body), then the
body is resolved. The captured variables' references in the enclosing scope are
resolved before binding them inside. On exit the scope is restored.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_closure" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Resolve the use(...) capture sources in the enclosing scope first.
    Let uses be proc attr with node, "uses"
    If uses is not equal to 0:
        Let ucount be proc list_length from ListOps with uses
        Let u be 0
        While u is less than ucount:
            Let use_node be proc list_get from ListOps with uses, u
            If use_node is not equal to 0:
                Let cap_name be proc attr with use_node, "name"
                If cap_name is not equal to 0:
                    Let bound be proc is_variable_bound with analyzer, cap_name
                    If bound is equal to 0:
                        proc add_semantic_warning with analyzer, "closure captures unbound variable"
                    End If
                End If
            End If
            Set u to u plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Let mark be proc scope_mark with analyzer

    Let params be proc attr with node, "params"
    proc bind_params with analyzer, params

    Note: Bind the captured names inside the closure scope.
    If uses is not equal to 0:
        Let ucount2 be proc list_length from ListOps with uses
        Let u2 be 0
        While u2 is less than ucount2:
            Let use_node2 be proc list_get from ListOps with uses, u2
            If use_node2 is not equal to 0:
                Let cap_name2 be proc attr with use_node2, "name"
                If cap_name2 is not equal to 0:
                    proc bind_variable with analyzer, cap_name2
                End If
            End If
            Set u2 to u2 plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Let body be proc attr with node, "body"
    If body is not equal to 0:
        Let inner be proc attr with body, "body"
        proc analyze_node_list with analyzer, inner
    End If

    proc scope_restore with analyzer, mark
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Binds every parameter's variable name into scope and resolves each parameter's
default expression at the enclosing scope (defaults cannot reference other
parameters). A promoted-property param (non-empty visibility) still binds its
$name like any other parameter.
@End Reasoning
Process called "bind_params" takes analyzer as Integer, params as Integer returns Integer:
    If params is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from ListOps with params
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let param be proc list_get from ListOps with params, i
        If param is not equal to 0:
            Let default be proc attr with param, "default"
            If default is not equal to 0:
                proc analyze_node with analyzer, default
            End If
            Let name be proc attr with param, "name"
            If name is not equal to 0:
                proc bind_variable with analyzer, name
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A foreach resolves its collection, then binds its key var (when present) and its
value var (the value var may be a list() destructuring target whose inner targets
all bind), then resolves the body. The loop variables persist into the body, which
is foreach's semantics.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_foreach" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let collection be proc attr with node, "collection"
    If collection is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_node with analyzer, collection
    End If

    Let key_var be proc attr with node, "key_var"
    If key_var is not equal to 0:
        proc bind_assign_target with analyzer, key_var
    End If

    Let value_var be proc attr with node, "value_var"
    If value_var is not equal to 0:
        proc bind_assign_target with analyzer, value_var
    End If

    Let body be proc attr with node, "body"
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_node with analyzer, body
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A catch clause binds its exception variable (when named) and resolves its caught
type names and body. The bound variable persists into the body.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_catch" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let var be proc attr with node, "var"
    If var is not equal to 0:
        Let var_len be proc string_length from StringCore with var
        If var_len is greater than 0:
            proc bind_variable with analyzer, var
        End If
    End If

    Let body be proc attr with node, "body"
    If body is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_node with analyzer, body
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A member access ($obj->prop or $obj->{$expr}) resolves its object expression. The
property slot is a STRING when not computed and a sub-node when computed, so it is
only descended into when the computed flag is set; reading the string slot as a
node dereferences garbage.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_member" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let object be proc attr with node, "object"
    If object is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_node with analyzer, object
    End If
    Let computed be proc attr with node, "computed"
    If computed is equal to 1:
        Let prop be proc attr with node, "property"
        If prop is not equal to 0:
            proc analyze_node with analyzer, prop
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A static member access (Class::member or Class::{$expr}) resolves its class_name
expression. The member slot is a STRING when not computed and a sub-node when
computed, so it is only descended into under the computed flag, exactly like
analyze_member.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_static_member" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let class_name be proc attr with node, "class_name"
    If class_name is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_node with analyzer, class_name
    End If
    Let computed be proc attr with node, "computed"
    If computed is equal to 1:
        Let member be proc attr with node, "member"
        If member is not equal to 0:
            proc analyze_node with analyzer, member
        End If
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A global statement binds each of its vars (variable nodes) into the current scope.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_var_binding_list" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let vars be proc attr with node, "vars"
    If vars is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from ListOps with vars
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let v be proc list_get from ListOps with vars, i
        If v is not equal to 0:
            proc bind_assign_target with analyzer, v
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
A static statement binds each static_var_item's name and resolves its default
expression.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_static_var" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let vars be proc attr with node, "vars"
    If vars is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from ListOps with vars
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let item be proc list_get from ListOps with vars, i
        If item is not equal to 0:
            Let default be proc attr with item, "default"
            If default is not equal to 0:
                proc analyze_node with analyzer, default
            End If
            Let name be proc attr with item, "name"
            If name is not equal to 0:
                proc bind_variable with analyzer, name
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
An assignment resolves its value expression, then binds its target (a plain
variable, an index/member lvalue whose base resolves, or a list() destructuring
whose inner targets all bind). This is what makes a subsequently-read variable
resolve, modelling PHP's create-on-first-assignment semantics.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_assign" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value be proc attr with node, "value"
    If value is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_node with analyzer, value
    End If

    Let target be proc attr with node, "target"
    If target is not equal to 0:
        proc bind_assign_target with analyzer, target
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Binds the variables introduced by an assignment/foreach/global target. A plain
variable binds its name. A list() or array destructuring binds each of its element
values recursively. An index or member lvalue (e.g. $a[0] = ..., $o->p = ...)
binds nothing new but resolves its base expression so the base variable is checked.
@End Reasoning
Process called "bind_assign_target" takes analyzer as Integer, target as Integer returns Integer:
    If target is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let nt be proc node_type_of with target
    If nt is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "variable":
        Let name be proc attr with target, "name"
        If name is not equal to 0:
            proc bind_variable with analyzer, name
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "list_pattern":
        proc bind_destructure_elements with analyzer, target
        Return 1
    End If

    If proc string_equals from StringCore with nt, "array":
        proc bind_destructure_elements with analyzer, target
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: index / member / static_member lvalue: resolve the base expression.
    proc analyze_node with analyzer, target
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Binds each element value of a list()/[] destructuring target. Each element is an
array_item whose value is itself a target (a variable or a nested destructuring),
and whose key (when present) is an ordinary expression that is resolved.
@End Reasoning
Process called "bind_destructure_elements" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let elements be proc attr with node, "elements"
    If elements is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let count be proc list_length from ListOps with elements
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let item be proc list_get from ListOps with elements, i
        If item is not equal to 0:
            Let key be proc attr with item, "key"
            If key is not equal to 0:
                proc analyze_node with analyzer, key
            End If
            Let value be proc attr with item, "value"
            If value is not equal to 0:
                proc bind_assign_target with analyzer, value
            End If
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: REFERENCE RESOLUTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Resolves a variable reference. A bound variable (parameter, prior assignment,
loop/catch/global/static binding) or a superglobal/$this resolves cleanly. Anything
else is recorded as a warning rather than an error: PHP creates variables lazily so
an unbound read is suspicious but not provably wrong.
@End Reasoning
Process called "resolve_variable" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let name be proc attr with node, "name"
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let bound be proc is_variable_bound with analyzer, name
    If bound is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    proc add_semantic_warning with analyzer, "unbound variable reference"
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves a class/function/constant name reference. A name that is a declared name
or a recognised built-in/reserved class resolves cleanly. Anything else is recorded
as a warning: the referenced symbol may be imported via use or autoloaded, so an
unknown bare name is suspicious but not provably wrong.
@End Reasoning
Process called "resolve_name" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let value be proc attr with node, "value"
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let defined be proc is_name_defined with analyzer, value
    If defined is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let builtin be proc is_builtin_class with value
    If builtin is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If

    proc add_semantic_warning with analyzer, "unresolved name reference"
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Generic recursion for nodes that are not scope-introducing. Resolves the standard
named single-expression slots and expression-list slots, plus positional children,
so every reachable variable and name reaches its resolver. The slot set is the
union of every attribute key the dict-AST contract defines that can hold an
expression or expression list, so no sub-expression is skipped.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_generic" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: single-expression slots
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "expr"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "value"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "condition"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "then"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "else"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "left"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "right"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "operand"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "object"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "callee"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "class_name"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "anon_class"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "index"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "collection"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "discriminant"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "key"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "test"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "level"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "arg"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "body"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "then_branch"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "else_branch"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "finally"
    proc analyze_attr_node with analyzer, node, "default"

    Note: expression-list slots
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "args"
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "elements"
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "conditions"
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "arms"
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "cases"
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "elseifs"
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "catches"
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "init"
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "update"
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "body"
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "members"
    proc analyze_attr_list with analyzer, node, "params"

    Note: positional children, if any
    Let children be proc get_ast_children from Parser with node
    If children is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_node_list with analyzer, children
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves a single named-attribute sub-node when present and when it is an AST node
(not a plain string). A node carries a "node_type" attribute; a plain string
attribute (e.g. an operator) does not, so node_type_of returns 0 and it is skipped.
Null-safe.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_attr_node" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let child be proc attr with node, key
    If child is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let child_nt be proc node_type_of with child
    If child_nt is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    proc analyze_node with analyzer, child
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves a single named-attribute list of sub-nodes when present. The list holds
AST nodes; condition lists may also hold plain expressions which analyze_node
handles. Null-safe.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_attr_list" takes analyzer as Integer, node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lst be proc attr with node, key
    If lst is not equal to 0:
        proc analyze_node_list with analyzer, lst
    End If
    Return 1
End Process
